Name: record
Version: 1.0.0
Cabal-Version: >=1.8.0.2
Build-Type: Simple
License: BSD3
License-File: LICENSE
Copyright: 2014 Gabriel Gonzalez
Author: Gabriel Gonzalez
Maintainer: Gabriel439@gmail.com
Bug-Reports: https://github.com/Gabriel439/Haskell-Record-Library/issues
Synopsis: Command line utility to document command environments and output
Description: This package creates the @record@ executable that you can use to
  wrap other commands to record the following information in @~/.record@:
  .
  * The current @git@ branch
  .
  * The current @git@ SHA
  .
  * The current @git@ diff
  .
  * The current @hostname@
  .
  * The current directory
  .
  * The current date and time
  .
  * The current user
  .
  * All command output, prefixing @stdout@ lines with @"O: "@ and @stderr@
    lines with @"E: "@
  .
  To use this tool, just prefix your shell commands with @record@
Category: Control, Concurrency
Source-Repository head
    Type: git
    Location: https://github.com/Gabriel439/Haskell-Record-Library

Executable record
    Hs-Source-Dirs: src
    Build-Depends:
        base            >= 4       && < 5  ,
        system-fileio   >= 0.2.1   && < 0.4,
        mvc             >= 1.0.0   && < 1.1,
        pipes           >= 4.0.0   && < 4.2,
        process         >= 1.0.1.1 && < 1.3,
        system-filepath >= 0.3.1   && < 0.5,
        transformers    >= 0.2.0.0 && < 0.5
    Main-Is: Record.hs
    GHC-Options: -O2 -Wall
